The paper deals with visual-inertial initialization, which is a problem in robotics and computer vision. The use of inertial measurements and optimization techniques suggests that the paper could belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) or Systems and Control (cs.SY) categories. The use of visual data and machine learning techniques suggests that the paper could also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV), Machine Learning (cs.LG), or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories.
